HEADWORD: Scuppernong
<hw>Scup"per*nong</hw> <pr>(sk⟦ucr⟧p"p⟦etil⟧r*n⟦ocr⟧ng)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably of American Indian origin.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An American grape, a form of <spn>Vitis
vulpina</spn>, found in the Southern Atlantic States, and often
cultivated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

